Olunga has not responded to those requests which normally flood his social media pages when he posts something.
In the past, Olunga has not hidden his love for Arsenal. He recorded a video of himself in December 2015 and posted on YouTube requesting Frenchman Arsene Wenger for a chance to play for Arsenal.
“Hi Arsene Wenger. I’m Michael Olunga Ogada, a striker at Gor Mahia FC which is in Kenya. I’m currently the best player in Kenya. I’ve scored 38 goals all season and my dream is to play for Arsenal,” said Olunga, who was 21 at the time.
Olunga hoped Wenger would consider his request and was even ready to join the feeder team.
“I’ll be sure to repay you for having faith in me. Thanks for considering my options,” he said.
Golden Boot
If he ever goes to Europe, it will not be his first time. When his request to Wenger failed, he found a new home in Swedish top-tier side Djurgardens IF in February 2016. Olunga has also played in La Liga for Girona on a season-long loan from Chinese outfit Guizhou Zhicheng.
He left Guizhou for Kashiwa on August 2018 and has been in scintillating form ever since.
Olunga scored 27 goals and provided nine assists in 2019 as coach Nelsinho’s side returned to the big-league as second-tier champions.



